        {
            "type": "h2-post",
            "content": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": " The <b><i>Konjunktiv II Präteritum</i></b>, also refered as just <b><i>Konjunktiv II</i></b>, is a unique verb form in German that used to express hypothetical scenarios and indirect speech. It might seem daunting at first, but understanding its formation and usage will improve your understanding of German grammar."
        },
        {
            "type": "callout",
            "content": "The <i>Konjunktiv II Präteritum</i> is mostly used on a few verbs that must be memorised. On the rest of verbs the Konjunktiv II form with \"werden\" will be used."
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Usage"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "We use the <i>Konjunktiv II Präteritum</i> tense to:"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Politeness:</b> it softens the speech when making polite requests or suggestions.",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Könnten Sie das Fenster schließen?",
                            "text": "Example: $__Könnten-können[verb-link-hover]__$ Sie das Fenster $__schließen-schließen[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(Could you close the window?)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>General Hypotheticals:</b> it addresses conditions that are imaginary or contrary to fact, not necessarily situated in the past",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Wenn ich König wäre!",
                            "text": "Example: Wenn ich König $__wäre-sein[verb-link-hover]__$!",
                            "translation": "(If I were king!)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Wishes:</b> It expresses wishes or scenarios that are desired yet not real.",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ach, wäre das schön!",
                            "text": "Example: Ach, $__wäre-sein[verb-link-hover]__$ das schön!",
                            "translation": "(Oh, that would be nice!)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Conjugation"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The <i>Konjunktiv II Präteritum</i> is mostly used with <b>modal verbs and the irregular verbs sein and haben</b>. For the rest of the verbs, the <a href='/lessons/kojunktiv-II-futur-I'>Konjunktiv II Futur I</a> form with \"werden\" will be used."
        },
        {
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Verbs used on the Konjunktiv II Präteritum"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The verbs that are conjugated in the <i>Konjunktiv II Präteritum</i> tense are: $__sein-sein[verb-link-hover]__$, $__haben-haben[verb-link-hover]__$, $__können-können[verb-link-hover]__$, $__mögen-mögen[verb-link-hover]__$, $__wollen-wollen[verb-link-hover]__$, $__sollen-sollen[verb-link-hover]__$ and $__dürfen-dürfen[verb-link-hover]__$."
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "We will always add the endings <b data-verb-prefix>-te</b>, <b data-verb-prefix>-test</b>, <b data-verb-prefix>-te</b>, <b data-verb-prefix>-ten</b>, <b data-verb-prefix>-tet</b>, <b data-verb-prefix>-ten</b>, except on the verb $__sein-sein[verb-link-hover]__$, where the <b data-verb-prefix>t</b> will be removed."
        },
